"{\"uid\": \"today.com-news-paris-olympics-bob-the-cap-catcher-swimming-rcna163989\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"A Michael Kors Bag, Suede Slippers and More Holiday Gifts at Walmart - Starting at $9    Maddie Ellis  Weekend Editor  When the world needed him most ... he was there.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 167, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 89, \"end\": 95, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maddie_Ziegler\", \"score\": 0.9999999970375484, \"rank\": 2.9625152143074655e-09, \"text\": \"Maddie\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maddie_Ziegler\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maddie_Ziegler\"}, {\"begin\": 96, \"end\": 101, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Havelock_Ellis\", \"score\": 0.9370166496695647, \"rank\": 0.06620790892873904, \"text\": \"Ellis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Havelock_Ellis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Havelock_Ellis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After Team USA's Emma Weber lost her swim cap during the women's 100-meter breaststroke preliminary race July 28, a hero answered the call.\", \"from\": 169, \"to\": 308, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 175, \"end\": 183, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"score\": 0.679862319581966, \"rank\": 0.3123180783240076, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\"}, {\"begin\": 186, \"end\": 190, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Swan\", \"score\": 0.9930345447681667, \"rank\": 0.006984358674250333, \"text\": \"Emma\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Swan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Swan\"}, {\"begin\": 191, \"end\": 196, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Weber\", \"score\": 0.6614918472696507, \"rank\": 0.5072416996402305, \"text\": \"Weber\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Weber\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Weber\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Although, as NBC announcers pointed out, Weber likely already had a second swim cap on her head, a man wearing a bright floral Speedo confidently walked onto the pool deck to save the day.\", \"from\": 310, \"to\": 498, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 323, \"end\": 326, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"score\": 0.9799306079420811, \"rank\": 0.011578590532298243, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\"}, {\"begin\": 351, \"end\": 356, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Weber\", \"score\": 0.6614918472696507, \"rank\": 0.5072416996402305, \"text\": \"Weber\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Weber\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Weber\"}, {\"begin\": 437, \"end\": 443, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Speedo\", \"score\": 0.9999999999402007, \"rank\": 5.986127043195458e-11, \"text\": \"Speedo\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Speedo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Speedo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After a pause in the competition, the man, who the Associated Press identified as a lifeguard, dove to the bottom of the nearly 10-foot pool and quickly grabbed the cap before surfacing.\", \"from\": 500, \"to\": 686, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 551, \"end\": 567, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"score\": 0.9998560426204977, \"rank\": 0.00014397804010724392, \"text\": \"Associated Press\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As he exited the pool, he held the cap up in triumph while waving to a cheering crowd.\", \"from\": 688, \"to\": 774, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Dubbed \\\"Bob the Cap Catcher,\\\" the brief moment amid Sunday's swim events has captured fans' hearts.\", \"from\": 776, \"to\": 875, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Who do you call when a swim cap falls in the pool?\", \"from\": 877, \"to\": 928, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"BOB THE CAP CATCHER,\\\" the NBC Olympics & Paralympics X accountposted Sunday.\", \"from\": 929, \"to\": 1005, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"He's an icon he's a legend he is the moment,\\\"one X user wrote, to which theNBC Olympics account responded,\\\"Main character energy.\\\"\", \"from\": 1007, \"to\": 1138, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The account for the next Summer Games, set for 2028 in Los Angeles, also celebrated the day's hero, writing, \\\"Thank you for your service, Bob.\\\"\", \"from\": 1140, \"to\": 1283, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1195, \"end\": 1206, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999937183475, \"rank\": 3.93348747907915e-09, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"NBC Olympics alsoshared footage of the moment to TikTok,receiving comments like, \\\"not all heroes wear...much of anything\\\" and, \\\"LOVE YOU BOB THE CAP CATCHER!!\\\"\", \"from\": 1285, \"to\": 1444, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1285, \"end\": 1297, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"NBC Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\"}, {\"begin\": 1334, \"end\": 1340, \"title\"